-- Iran Says Economy Is `Strong;' Plans 12 Billion-Euro Islamic Bond Sale
-- Rakteem Katakey
-- 2010-07-08T06:31:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/iran-says-economy-is-strong-plans-12-billion-euro-islamic-bond-sale.html

          
          
             Sanctions haven’t hurt Iran’s
“strong and robust” economy, and energy prices and agriculture
will power growth, Finance Minister Shamseddin Hosseini told
reporters in New Delhi today. The nation has the approval of its
lawmakers to sell 12 billion euros of Islamic bonds, he said.  
